      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see where we\u0027re forcing the length of the SkString back to zero? You\u0027re overwriting part of the existing bytes without updating the string length, which seems bad. Note that SkString isn\u0027t actually \u0027\\0\u0027 terminated, it just keeps the extra \u0027\\0\u0027 around for easy conversion to c string, the SkString is a pointer and length (as all UTF-8 must be, codepoint zero is a perfectly cromulent codepoint and must be handled as one and not as a terminator).",
      "revId": "b3833f72eacacc70e8b17afd59c591633869c981",
